The paper proposes a framework for transcribing content from structural images, which involves image recognition and language modeling. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques, such as grammar modeling, which suggests it could also belong to the computational linguistics (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
